<TITLE> RU teachers skip classes for a free Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, July 26 (bdnews24.com)  As many as 200 teachers at Rajshahi University skipped classes en bloc Thursday demanding freedom of detained Awami League chief Sheikh Hasina. The teachers applied for leave to the chairmen of the departments Wednesday to go on leave Thursday. The scheduled examinations, however, were held although most students stayed off the campus. Professor Abdus Sobhan of applied physics and electronics told bdnews24.com that they had taken leave from academic activities also to demand national elections without delay, an end to restrictions on politics and educational institutions free of corruption. bdnews24.c
